  "text": "The methods used have been described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Each rat received six solid, stainless steel beads, diameter (d) ϭ 1.4 mm (Bal-tec, Los Angeles, CA) via oral gavage in 2 ml of 15% barium sulfate in slurry form (E-Z-HD 98% wt/wt; Cat. No. 764; E-Z-EM Canada, kindly provided by Palmerston North Hospital, New Zealand). Note that for the bead size comparison experiments smaller beads (d ϭ 1.1 mm) were also used. Isoflurane anesthesia was induced in a chamber and persisted for 5 min during which gavage was performed upon recovery of the swallow reflex.",
